      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Ring-opening of the <i>trans</i>-cyclobutene isomer shown takes place at much lower temperature than a similar ring-opening of the <i>cis</i>-cyclobutene isomer. Explain the temperature effect, and identify the stereochemistry of each reaction as either conrotatory or disrotatory.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZzRhIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--65ee0dca65b5b8022db1e6be52a1521cdb7cca61/OChem_30_EC_022.jpg\" alt=\"Cis cyclobutene reacts at 300 degree Celsius to give two cyclobutene rings fused by a bond. This reacts at 100 degree Celsius to give trans cyclobutene.\">",
